column4: Damn, I'm curious what exactly the feds look for to constitute 'suspicious ATM' activity to behind investigating them to begin with? Crazy that's how they ended up on law enforcements radar.

Same with an IRL dealer...you have no idea if they are in the house across the street or car up the road recording license plates or pictures. 

At least with DNM if you keep your mouth shut and cover your tracks they can't prove that a package of drugs mailed to your address was ordered by you.  

Still if I had ever used this market I would be shitting my pants and burning my computer right now.

LE go up the chain, not down. Unless they have evidence you were bulk buying in obvious resale amounts they're not gonna waste the time and money raiding you over being associated with a DNM vendor. More likely they care more about figuring who the vendor was ordering their product from (although since they were pressing with fent it'll be from China so it's not like they can do much).
